&lt;p&gt;This does get me the built-in login form at &lt;tt&gt;/login&lt;/tt&gt;, but it also hijacks &lt;tt&gt;/foo/something/login&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;tt&gt;DefaultLoginPageGeneratingFilter#matches&lt;/tt&gt; appears to treat the &lt;tt&gt;url&lt;/tt&gt; as a suffix instead of as an absolute path. Even though the context path should be &lt;tt&gt;/foo/something/login&lt;/tt&gt;, the conditional at 262 evaluates to &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;, and the &lt;tt&gt;endsWith&lt;/tt&gt; comparison is used. I can&apos;t get Eclipse to dump the contents of &lt;tt&gt;request.getContextPath()&lt;/tt&gt; right there during debugging.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
